In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. commemorates Gold Star Mother's and Family's Day, expressing his condolences and gratitude to the families who have lost loved ones in military service. He emphasizes the importance of caring for these families and fulfilling the nation's promise to support military and veteran families, caregivers, and survivors. President Biden highlights the sacrifices made by generations of brave men and women who fought for the idea of the United States of America and helped establish a nation grounded in freedom, democracy, equality, tolerance, opportunity, and justice. He pledges to continue honoring their legacies and working towards a more perfect union. The article concludes with the official proclamation of Gold Star Mother's and Family's Day and a call for government officials and the American people to display the flag and hold appropriate ceremonies to show gratitude and respect for Gold Star Mothers and Families.